description:
&lt;p&gt;A rare opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic, dynamic, caring and compassionate and dedicated Band 2 Health Carer to join our inpatient Rehab team at Fordingbridge Hospital. The inpatient team aspires to provide a responsive, safe effective caring service that is well led.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To support you within your role, Southern Health NHS Trust have an excellent development and learning programme to help further develop your clinical skills. The Trust knows that supporting, developing and nurturing their staff leads to outstanding patient care. We are committed to support the development of your career and have a competency based approach to clinical training and development which will ensure you are able to apply your newly developed skills in a safe and effective way.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work as part of an inpatient nursing/therapy team involved in Patient’s rehab to enable them to achieve their individual goals in order to be discharged safely from hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fordingbridge Hospital is a community hospital based in the town of Fordingbridge, within Southern Health NHS Foundation Trust. Southern health is currently rated good overall by the CQC. Informal visits are encouraged.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested in joining us or would like more information please contact Sue Findlay ward manager or Vanessa Amey ward sister on 01425 651414&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Happy to talk flexible working&lt;/strong&gt;-&lt;strong&gt; all requests for flexible and part time working will be considered.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Follow us on Facebook and on Twitter:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
